02/08/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- A group of Slovak soldiers serving with KFOR has been caught smuggling cigarettes and alcohol from Kosovo, the Slovak Defence Ðinistry confirmed on Wednesday (August 1st).
About 450 litres of alcohol and 321 cartons of cigarettes were found last week in the luggage of 132 soldiers, in a truck bound from the Sajkovac base to Slovakia.
The country's General Staff plans to establish a special commission to investigate the case.
(Beta, B92 - 01/08/07)
